cs.SI, cs.NI, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.CL 

This paper is likely to belong to the cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) sub-category as it deals with user behaviour analysis based on traffic log in wireless networks, which is related to social network analysis. It could also belong to cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) as it deals with wireless networks. Additionally, it could belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as it uses TF-IDF weighing to form a feature matrix. It could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it uses K-means++ clustering algorithm and LSA for dimensionality reduction. Finally, it could belong to cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with document classification problems.
